    <briefdescription>
<para><ref refid="class_rms_store" kindref="compound">RmsStore</ref> class derived from task base class. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para><simplesect kind="par"><title>Detailed Description </title><para>The RMS storage class is responsible to store the received RMS and hit values from RMS task and to forward them to the data manager task. On receiving a RMS report request from power manager task, the request shall be also forwarded to the data manager task. The RMS storage class provides a store and reset method and methods to print out the data for testing purposes. <bold>Message Interaction:</bold><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Receive<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>RMS task</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Power manager task</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>RMS storage (self, callback function for shell command &apos;r&apos;)</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Transmit<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Data manager task</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>RMS storage (self, callback function for shell command &apos;r&apos;) </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
